<TITLE> Savar road crash kills 5 of a family </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, May 27 (bdnews24.com)Five members of a family died and another five passengers were injured when a bus drove into a van near Barhoiparha bus stand on Nabinagar-Kaliakoir road on Wednesday morning. The dead were identified as van driver Ariful Islam, 30 and passengers Saiful Islam, 32, his sisters Nazma Begum, 40, and Shefali Begum, 38 and Shefali's daughter Annie, 15, all from Jamurki of Mirzapur under Tangail district. Sheikh Saadi, sub-inspector of Ashulia Police Station, told bdnews24.com that the van carrying nine passengers of a Jamurki family was travelling to Zia International Airport in Dhaka to receive their relatives due to return home from abroad. At around 7:15am, when they reached Barhoiparha bus stand, an oncoming passenger bus hit it, almost crumpled the smaller vehicle and fled the scene. The crash left four of the family and the driver dead on the spot and injuring the five other passengers. The injured were admitted to local hospitals for treatment. Their condition remains critical too, police said. The wrecked vehicle was carried to the police station. bdn
